plan folders are created through multiple uncontrolled paths (agent Write tool, cmd_scaffold,
cmd_create) that bypass the CLI's plan init pipeline. The workspace file is a symptom —
the real issue is that Claude sessions and spawned agents jump directly to creating plan
artifacts without going through `agentic plan init`, which is the only path that properly
creates worktrees AND updates the workspace file.

SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE: Every plan folder in docs/plans/live/ was created by `agentic plan init`,
has a corresponding worktree (or explicitly opted out), and the workspace file stays in sync
automatically without manual intervention.

